1984 MAY 25<br>
<br>
KAUPUS, DAVID<br>
<br>
A man who leaped to his death from the Narrows Bridge Thursday was identified today as David Kapus 38, of Olympia. (Tacoma News Tribune May 26, 1984).<br>
<br>
The body of an Olympia man was recovered by a Tacoma fireboat crew in water near the Narrows Bridge yesterday afternoon following a report that the man had jumped off the bridge.  The man is believed to have parked his car about mid-span on the bridge and jumped about 11:20 a.m..  The fireboat crew recovered his body about ninety minutes later. (Tacoma News Tribune May 25,1984).<br>
<br>
