<H3><IMG SRC="board.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></H3>
<HR>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<I>The Tacoma Public Library is governed by an independent  five-member
Board of Trustees appointed by the Mayor of the City of Tacoma.
All meetings of the Library's Board of Trustees are open to the
public. Individuals are welcome to attend meetings and speak to
the Trustees regarding their concerns. </I>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<I>Two-hour free parking is available in a library parking lot
one block south of the library at the corner of 12th and Tacoma
Avenue South. </I>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<I><B>For more information </B>about meetings of the Library's
Trustees contact the Library's Community Relations Office at (206)
591-5688. </I>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<I>The Library's mission and responsibilities.</I>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

