<BODY>

<H4><IMG SRC="kids4.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><A NAME="topofpage"></A>
</H4>
<HR>

<H4><A HREF="kids.htm">Return to Tacoma Public Library's Just For Kids Home Page  </A>
<BR>
<A HREF="../index.htm">Return to Tacoma Public Library's Home Page</a></H4>
<HR>

<H3>Cool books for kids!</H3>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.ucalgary.ca/%7Edkbrown/awards.html">Children's Literature Award Lists</a><BR>
Find the books that won awards chosen by other children as well
as awards from the US, Canada, and England, including recent Caldecott
and Newberry Medal winners plus international awards recipients.
Also, local kids may learn how to choose their own favorite book
to win the Pacific Northwest Library Association's Young Reader's
Choice Award.
</UL>

<P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.winternet.com/~ogrosman/BOOKHOUSE/BooklistT.html">Girls and Women as Strong Characters</a><BR>
Dynamite list of both picture and juvenile books that will do
any female's heart good. Forget the wimpy princess waiting to
be rescued - these ladies take care of themselves!
</UL>

<P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://funnelweb.utcc.utk.edu/~epling/readaloud.html">Read Aloud! A Guide to Reading Children's Books</a> <BR>
Wonderful lists of books to share, split up into age groups: babies
&amp; toddlers, ages 3-5, ages 5-7, ages 7-9, ages 9-11, and ages
11-13. Also has a great list of the benefits of reading aloud
if you need to nudge or coerce your parents.
</UL>

<P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.bookwire.com/pw/bsl/childrens/current.childrens.html">Publisher's Weekly Children's Bestseller List</A> <BR>
Wonder what just EVERYBODY'S reading? Here are the current bestsellers
for kids, along with a link to the all-time bestselling kids books
ever - how many have YOU read?
</UL>

<P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.docker.com/~whiteheadm/yaread.html">Young Adult Reading</a><BR>
Lists and reviews of young adult books for teens.
</UL>

<P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://iquest.com/~e-media/kv/poetry.html">Positively Poetry!</a><BR>
This Web page, created by 13-year-old Kellie Vaughn of Huntsville,
Alabama, is devoted to the poetry of young people. She accepts
work from kids around the world, publishes her own poetry and
updates the page regularly.
</UL>

<P>
