<P>
<I>Welcome to the Tacoma Public Library's</I> Just for Kids'<I>
Reference and Information Page.<BR>
This is the perfect place to be if you're insatiably curious about
the world around you, need help finding information for school
projects, or generally want to know what's what. New sites and
subject areas added on a regular basis. </I>
<P>
<A HREF="#History">American History</A> --/--<A HREF="#Animals">Animals</A>--/--<A HREF="#Reference">General Reference</A>--/--<A HREF="#Government">Government</A>--/--<A HREF="#Literature">Literature</A>
<BR>
<A HREF="#Maps">Maps</A>--/--<A HREF="#Misc">Miscellaneous</A>--/--<A HREF="#Native">Native Americans</A>--/--<A HREF="#Science">Science</A>--/--<A HREF="#Sports">Sports</A>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="#search">Other ways of finding information on the WWW (a link to a variety of WWW searching tools)</A>

<LI>Information about Tacoma and the Pacific Northwest<BR>
(a link to the Tacoma Public Library Special Collections Home
Page)
</UL>

<H4><A HREF="kids.htm">Return to Tacoma Public Library's Just for Kids Home Page</A>
