<HEAD>
<TITLE>Kids Site of the Month</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFE8">
<P ALIGN="CENTER"><A NAME="top"></A></P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER"><IMG SRC="cool.gif" WIDTH="482" HEIGHT="147"></P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER"></P>
<HR>      
<P ALIGN="CENTER"><B>Return to : <A HREF="kids.htm">Just For Kids </A>  |
<A HREF="../index.htm"><B>Tacoma Public Library Home </B></A></B></P>
<HR>
<H4> October's site of the month!</H4>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><IMG
SRC="gecko.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE" WIDTH="31" HEIGHT="22"><A HREF="http://www.primenet.com/~hodges/kids_crambo.html">Huh?!</a>.  <BR>Back to school means reading, writing,
Ever play CRAMBO?  How about ZIGGY PIGGY? Could I interest you in a quick game of
DOGGEREL?  Wander on over and take a peek at these bodacious word games for kids like you.</P>
<HR>
<H3>Previous sites of the month!</H3>
<HR>
<H4> September's site of the month!</H4>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><IMG SRC="gecko.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE" WIDTH="31" HEIGHT="22"><A HREF="http://www.historychannel.com/kids/kids.html">History
for Kids from The History Channel</a>.  <BR>Back to school means reading, writing,
arithmetic AND history! History can be cool. Really...just check out this site
(especially for kids) from the History Channel.  Learn about what happened on
this day in hostry, check out nifty drawings of National Historic Landmarks, and
lots of other neat stuff.</P>
<HR>
<H6>August's  site of the month!</H6>
<P><IMG SRC="gecko.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE" WIDTH="31" HEIGHT="22"><A HREF="www.tpymuseum.com">The
Toy Museum</a></P>
<P>Visit the home of Tony the Tiger, the Sugar Bear and the Trix Rabbit, and a
host of other toys housed at this Florida Museum dedicated to collecting  toys
used to advertise  commercial products (like cereal, for instance).</P>
<P></P>
<HR>
<H6>July's site of the month!</H6>
<P><IMG SRC="gecko.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE" WIDTH="31" HEIGHT="22"><A
HREF="http://www.cs.yale.edu/homes/sjl/froggy.html">The FROGGY page.</A></P>
<P>This is a really slimy site. Really slimy. Everything you ever (never?)
wanted to know about frogs. Frog pictures. Animated frogs. Famous frogs.
Net.frogs! Froggy sounds. Froggy pictures. Froggy tales. Scientific frogs. And
our favorite - Origami Jumping Frogs.</P>
<P></P>
<HR>
<H6>June, 1996</H6>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><IMG
SRC="gecko.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE" WIDTH="31" HEIGHT="22"><A
HREF="http://unitedmedia.com/comics/peanuts">The Peanuts Home Page</A><BR>Good
grief, Charlie Brown! Visit Lucy, Linus, Snoopy and all their friends at the
Peanuts Home Page. Lots of comics, Peanuts trivia and more!</P>
<HR>
<H6>May, 1996</H6>
<P><IMG SRC="gecko.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE" WIDTH="31" HEIGHT="22"><A
HREF="http://www.fn.net/~jmayans/lemonade">Lemonade Stand</A><BR>Okay, here's
the deal. You're a kid setting up his own Lemonade Stand in a neighbor's yard.
You want to make money. You want to make LOTS of money. Or, you'll go broke.
It's all in how you play the game.</P>
<HR>
<H6>April, 1996</H6>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><IMG
SRC="gecko.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE" WIDTH="31" HEIGHT="22"><A
HREF="http://ucunix.san.uc.edu/~edavis/kids-list/crafts/doughs.html">Let's Get
Messy!!!!!</A><BR>Recipes for play slime, 'gak,' Kool-Aid playdough, silly
putty, monster bubbles, and more. Have a blast!</P>
