<h6>Search Methods Available include:</h6>
<p><B>Browse Ship Names and Shipping Topics Starting With:</b> Look at an alphabetical list of Ships or Shipping information <i>beginning</i> with your word or phrase.
<br><B>Ship/Shipping Record Contains</b>: Search the Ship Name or Shipping field for a specific keyword or phrase.  Useful for finding every "peak" or "valley".
<br><B>Ship Name or Shipping Information is Exactly Like</b>: Search for an exact match on the Ship name.
<br><B>Ship/Shipping Sounding Like</b>: Use extended soundex or metaphone on the <i>first word</i> of the Ship name or Shipping-related topic 
to find possible matches when the correct spelling is not known.
<br><B>Description contains</B>: Search the descriptive field for the occurence of a keyword or phrase.  No boolean or special handling is used, and except for capitalization it looks
for the presence of the word or phrase entered.
<hr>
<p>This database currently includes a searchable index of more than
6,000 ships and full text information on 1,000 ships. Included here is information,
including name (and former names) of vessels, builder, career,
and disposition, on ships built on the Pacific coast, and ships
with a connection to the Pacific Northwest. <BR>
<A HREF="nwdata.htm">More information</A> on this and other projects is
available.
