<html><head><title>Tacoma Obituary Database</title>
<body>
<img src="obit.gif" align=middle alt="Tacoma Public Library - Northwest Reference (NWR) -- Tacoma Obituary Index">
<br><br><b>Please note</b>: this index is under construction.  It contains more than 150,000 individual obituary index records. The paper files are still being converted and this is a snapshot of
more up to date databases available at the Library.  This file is complete only through <b>lastname WHITE</b> for the 1960's,
while pre-1950 obituary coverage is still incomplete.  The latest entry is for the News Tribune of 31 January 1996.
Up-to-date electronic and paper files are available in the Northwest Room during normal library hours.<br>
<p>Entries are for the Tacoma News Tribune/Morning News Tribune unless some other source is specified.
<hr>
<form action="/cgi-win/obitscgi.exe/form" method="POST">
<PRE>
Search on Tacoma Obituaries: <SELECT NAME="searchby" SIZE=5><OPTION SELECTED>1. Name Starting With<OPTION>2. Name Containing (Slow Search)<OPTION>3. Death Date is<OPTION>4. Name Sounding Like <OPTION></SELECT>
Name or full Date: <input size=45 name="words">
</PRE>
<p><input type=submit value="Submit search"><input type=reset value="Clear">
<h6>Search Methods Available include:</h6>
<p><B>Browse Names Starting With:</b> Look at an alphabetical list of Names <i>beginning</i> with the name you entered.
<br><B>Name Contains keyword</b>: Search the Name field for a specific word.  Useful for finding first names or spelling uncertainties.  This is a <b>very slow</b> search.
<br><B>Death date is Exactly</b>: Search for an exact match on a specific death date.  Must include month, day and year in a common format.  Does not retrieve obiturary entries where the death date is not known or not indicated.
<br><B>Name Sounding Like</b>: Use extended soundex on the <i>last name</i> of the obituary record to find possible matches when the correct spelling is not known.
<hr>
<p>
This database is an index to Tacoma and Pierce County obituaries (currently
complete from 1984 to the present) that were published in the Tacoma News
Tribune. The full text of the obituaries are available in the
Main Library's Northwest Room &amp; Special Collections. If you cannot visit
the Library to locate a copy of an obituary, it is possible to request that
it be sent to you.  To obtain a copy of a specific obituary please send either a mail request to:<br>
<h5>Northwest Reference - Tacoma Public Library - 1102 Tacoma Ave South - Tacoma WA 98402<br></h5>
or an e-mail to the webfoot administrator.
<br><br>Make sure you include the name, death date (where available), and newspaper
citation.  Make sure you include your home address so we can mail hard copy
of the obituary to you.  The obituary information is stored on microfilm,
and cannot be returned to you via e-mail.  <b>We must have a mailing address. </b>
Up to 2 obituary records can be obtained for free.  For more than two we
request $1 for up to four records to cover copying and mailing costs.  Any
support of this project is gratefully appreciated.
<br>
