<TITLE>Get a Clue. Read!</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="David Domkoski">
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<BODY>

<H3><I>Get a Clue. Read!<A NAME="topofpage"></A><BR>
</I>Get ready for the Tacoma Public Library's <BR>
1996 Summer Reading Club!</H3>

<P>
<IMG SRC="inline.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> 
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<I>The ability to read is the basic stepping stone that insures
success in school and in the workplace. The Library's annual summer
reading program provides an important opportunity for young students
to continue to develop and maintain critical reading and comprehension
skills throughout the long summer months when they are not in
school. The annual summer reading program is the most important
thing we do at the Tacoma Public Library! <BR>
</I>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<H4><A HREF="intouch.htm">Return to InTouch, the Tacoma Public Library newsletter</A>
<BR>
<A HREF="../../index.htm">Return to Tacoma Public Library's HomePage</H4></a>
<HR>

<H4>How the Summer Reading Club Works. </H4>

<P>
You earn points (based on the number of pages) for every book
you read. The more books you read, the more points you earn. The
more points you earn, the more prizes you get. What could be easier
than that?
<P>
As a member of the club, you're expected to read at your own level.
All the books you report on must be checked out from the Tacoma
Public Library. While you can check out the books from any of
our ten locations, you can only report on books at the branch
library where you signed up to join the club.
<P>
There are lots of interesting books in the library, so the 'informal'
books - comic books, 'choose your own ending' books, cartoon books
and books that come with records or cassettes don't count. That
doesn't mean you can't read them, you just can't report on them
to earn points.
<P>
The rest is pretty simple. The first time you report you will
receive a colorful name tag that will help us (and you) keep track
of your reading. You can only make one report each day (although
there is no limit on the number of book on which you can report)
and all the books you are reporting on must be brought in and
shown to the library staff/volunteer.
<P>
Sometimes, when the library gets really busy, there may be lots
of kids waiting to report. If you can't wait, have your mom and
dad (or guardian) complete and sign a Summer Reading Club Reporting
Form. These forms are available at the SRC Reporting Desk. Return
the form to a library staff member (or volunteer) along with the
books you- listed on the form. That way, you'll get credit for
all the books you read. If you've read enough to earn a prize,
you'll want to report in person (or wait until next time to pick
up the prize).<A NAME="dates"></A> 
<H4><A HREF="#topofpage">Return to top of page</A></H4>
<HR>

<H4>Club dates</H4>

<P>
You can start reporting on Saturday, June 15, 1996.
<P>
The last day to report is Saturday, August 17, 1996.<A NAME="points"></A>
<HR>

<H4>Earning prizes</H4>

<P>
Now, the neat stuff about prizes. You receive points for the books
you read as follows:
<P>
All books marked ----- CJ -- 1 point
<P>
Up to 99 pages ----- 2 points
<P>
100 - 149 pages ------ 3 points
<P>
150 - 199 pages ------ 4 points
<P>
200 - 299 pages ----- 5 points
<P>
300 (or more) pages ----- 6 points
<P>
The more points you earn, the more prizes you earn.<A NAME="prizes"></A>

<H4><A HREF="#topofpage">Return to top of page</A></H4>
<HR>

<H4>1996 Prizes</H4>

<P>
This year we have terrific prizes, including:
<P>
5 points ------- A Get a clue. Read! button
<P>
10 points ------ A personal pan pizza from Godfather's Pizza
<P>
25 points ------ A rainbow pen
<P>
50 points ------ Super sports bottle
<P>
75 points ----- A slick slinky
<P>
100 points ----- An invitation to the Mayor's Award Ceremony and
a free book
<P>
125 points ----- One child &amp; one adult ticket to the <B>Point
Defiance Zoo &amp; Aquarium</B>, &amp; <B>Dinamation's Dig Those
Dinosaurs</B> exhibit!
<P>
150 points ----- Mayor's Award with Honor! And a Get a Clue. Read
baseball cap!<HR>

<P>
The Tacoma Public Library's Summer Reading Program is made possible
through funds raised during the Library's annual Monster Book
Sale.. All donations of used books are welcome and you can donate
books at any branch library.
<P>
The Tacoma Public Library reserves the right to substitute prizes
of an equal or greater value if necessary.
<P>
If you have any questions, call the Library's Community Relations
Office at (206) 591-5688.
<H4><A HREF="#topofpage">Return to top of page</A></H4>
<HR>

