<HEAD>

<TITLE>Beating the Overdue Book Blues</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="David Domkoski">
<META NAME="OPERATOR" CONTENT="David Domkoski">
</HEAD>

<BODY>
<A name="topofpage"></A>
<H2><IMG SRC="usingtag.gif" ALT="Using the Library" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

<H2>Beating the Overdue Book Blues</H2>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<CITE>It's Saturday afternoon and the neighborhood mailman just
filled your mailbox with letters, the latest issue of your favorite
magazine, a new catalog (yeah!), a postcard and - YIKES - overdue
notices from the library (sigh). You quickly add up the damage
- 7 compact discs from that terrifically long weekend last month...3
bestsellers you took with you on vacation way back when...the
six books you checked out for your son's September school report.
Ouch!</CITE> 
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<CITE>Does this sound all too familiar? If it does, here are some
tips on avoiding those pesky overdue fines.</CITE> 
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<H4><A HREF="loan.htm">Return to Loan Periods and Limits</A><BR>
<A HREF="polihome.htm">Return to Everything you need to know...</A>
<BR>
<A HREF="../index.htm">Return to Tacoma Public Library Home Page</A>
</H4>
<HR>

<UL>
<LI>Keep a library list on your refrigerator door, listing all
the books check out during your last library visit and the date
they are all due.
<LI>Create a special place in your home just for library materials,
ideally someplace where you can't help but see them every day.
When you finish with a book, return it to that spot. When it's
time for your next trip to the library, all your materials will
be in one place.
<LI>Keep a special library card for each child on his or her bedroom
door. List the books checked out, and their due date. Check or
cross out books that are returned. This makes a great reading
log for your child, too.
<LI>The next time you visit the library, request a print-out of
all the library books and other materials checked out on your
card. Library staff are always willing to provide print outs of
your records if the check out desk isn't too busy. You could even
call ahead a day or two and have one waiting for you!
<LI>Don't forget, if you can't make a visit to the library, you
can always renew your books over the telephone.
<LI>Library fines do not have to be an inevitable fact of life.
They can be easily avoided with a little planning. Try it sometimes
and beat the overdue book blues.
</UL>

<H4><A HREF="#topofpage">Return to top of page</A></H4>

