<HEAD><TITLE>Enter Magazine--The Digital Kitchen</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE><H2 ALIGN=CENTER><B>Mexican Potatoskins:</B></H2>



<P>For all of you out there in a rush, the ingredients for this recipe can all be prepared ahead and simply reheated when dinner time draws near.</P>



<B>

<P>4 large baking potatoes</P>





<P>1 pound of ground beef</P>





<P>taco seasoning</P>





<P>1 tomato</P>





<P>1 onion</P>





<P>shredded cheese (whatever kind you like)</P>





<P>salsa</P>





<P>sour cream</P>





<P>refried beans (optional):</P>

</B>

<BR>
<BR>



<FONT SIZE=4><P><B>Directions</B></P></FONT>


<P> 1. Bake the potatoes in an oven or microwave.</P>





<P>2. Cook the ground beef in a skillet. Rinse it in a strainer with hot water to remove excess fat. Return to the skillet and combine with the taco seasoning and follow the directions.</P>





<P>3. Chop the tomato and onion and set them aside in separate bowls.</P>





<P>4. Cut open the potato on a plate. Stuff with meat, toppings, salsa, sour cream and cheese. </P>
<BR>

<P>Copyright 1996, Enter Inc. http://www.entermag.com</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BR>
