<HEAD><TITLE>Enter Magazine--The Digital Kitchen</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"> 
<BR>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Macaroni and Meat		</H2>				

<BR>


<BLOCKQUOTE><P><B>Yield:</B> 2 entree portions or 4 sides</P>



<P><B>Time to Prepare:</B> about 20 minutes</P>


<BR>
<BR>

<B>

<P>1 box macaroni and cheese</P>




<P>1 can condensed tomato soup (low-fat and low-sodium if possible)</P>




<P>1 pound ground beef</P>




<P>Optional Ingredients: chili powder, hot sauce, onion</P></B>




<P><B>Directions:</B></P>





<P>1.  Brown the ground beef in a skillet on medium heat.  Cook until none of it is still pink.  Chop it fine with a spatula.</P>




<P>2. Dump meat into a strainer and run hot water over the beef to remove excess fat.  Set aside.</P>




<P>3. Prepare the macaroni and cheese according to directions.</P>




<P>4. Add ground beef and 1/2 can of condensed tomato soup (more or less to taste). </P>




<P>5. If desired, add onion (about 1/3 cup chopped), chili powder and hot sauce (to taste).</P>




<P>6. Set burner on low, cover the macaroni and meat. Heat for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.</P>



<B>Low-Fat Version </B>



<P>-Use lean ground beef (try to get no less than 90 percent lean)</P>




<P>- Use 1/2 as much butter or omit it all together when preparing the macaroni and cheese.</P>

<P>Copyright 1996, Enter Inc. http://www.entermag.com</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
