<BR>


<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Lemon Basil Fettucini (meatless)</H2><BR>




<BLOCKQUOTE><P><B>Yield:</B> About two servings</P>




<P><B>Time:</B> 30 - 45 minutes</P>


<BR>
<BR>




<B><P>1 cup broccoli florets, chopped</P>




<P>1 cup cauliflower florets, chopped</P>




<P>1/2 onion, cut into rings</P>




<P>1/2 cup chicken or vegetable broth</P>




<P>2 cups cooked fettucini noodles</P>




<P>1 tablespoon chopped fresh basil</P>






<P>2 tablespoons lemon juice </P>




<P>1 cup red pepper, chopped (about 1 pepper)
salt and pepper to taste</P>



<BR>
<BR>



<P>Directions:</P></B>





<P>1. Cook the broccoli, cauliflower, onion, red pepper, one tablespoon the lemon juice and 1/4 cup of broth in a skillet over medium heat (7-10 minutes), stirring often until the vegetables are crispy tender.</P>




<P>2. Stir in the remaining lemon juice, broth, pepper and cooked noodles.  Cook about five more minutes until the vegetables are tender.</P>






<P><B>Serving Suggestions:</B></P>





<P>- Serve with a simple salad of spinach leaves, grated carrot, radish and a dressing of lemon juice and honey with pepper.</P>




<P>- With the entree, serve toasted sourdough slices or garlic bread.</P>




<P>- Try any combination of fresh fruit.  Suggested fruits are: grapes, melon, blueberries, raspberries, strawberries, cherries, etc.</P>


<P>Copyright 1996, Enter Inc. http://www.entermag.com</P></BLOCKQUOTE>

