<HEAD><TITLE>Enter Magazine--The Digital Kitchen</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"> 
<BR>



<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Chocolate Carmel Pecan Ice Cream Pie
</H2><BR>

<BLOCKQUOTE>Here's a dessert that is perfect for company or just to enjoy all by yourself.  And guess what? It is sooooo easy!

<B>

<P>1 pre-made pie shell (graham or cookie)</P>





<P>1 quart vanilla ice cream or frozen yogurt</P>





<P>1 small package chocolate chips</P>



<P>1  small package pecan pieces</P>





<P>1 jar carmel ice cream topping </P>

</B>
<BR>
<BR>

<B>Directions</B>



<P>1. Pull ice cream out of the freezer and allow to thaw on the counter for about 1/2 hour.</P>





<P>2. Open the pie shell, but leave it in the foil tin.</P>





<P>3. Melt 1/2 cup of chocolate chips over a hot-water bath or in the microwave.  </P>





<P>4. Spread the chocolate evenly over the bottom of the pie crust.  Put it in the refrigerator to harden the chocolate.
</P>




<P>5. Spread the ice cream into the pie shell (on top of the chocolate).  Use only enough to almost reach the top edge of the shell.</P>

 



<P>6. Pour the carmel over the ice cream and smooth.  You probably won't need all the topping.</P>





<P>7. Sprinkle the pecans on top.  You could also sprinkle chocolate chips on if you want.  Freeze for two hours.</P>





<P>To serve, use a warm, wet knife to slice through the pie.  Garnish with whipped cream and serve.</P>



<B>*</B>Hot chocolate or flavored coffee goes well with this.




<P>Copyright 1996, Enter Inc. http://www.entermag.com</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BR>
