<HEAD><TITLE>Eneter Magazine--The Digital Kitchen</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"> 

<BR>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Baked Apples</H2>

<BR>


<BLOCKQUOTE><P>This old favorite is a deceptively simple recipe. It makes a sweet, enticing desert, or a spicey treat any afternoon.</P>







<P>1.	Take your favorite apple, core it and peel the top half. 
</P>




<P>2.	Place in a oven-safe container just large enough to hold the apple.
</P>




<P>3.	Fill the center with 1 teaspoon of butter or margarine, 1 teaspoon<BR>
 brown sugar, and 1/8 teaspoon cinnamon.
</P>




<P>4. 	Preheat oven at 350 degrees. Put apple in oven for 10 minutes. 
	Then baste the apple with the syrup in the bottom of the dish. </P>

	

<P>Bake for 10 more minutes.</P>







<P>5.	Repeat process until apple is tender when poked with a fork.</P>





<P>6.	Remove from oven carefully. Sprinkle more brown sugar if
 	desired.</P>


<P>Variations on a theme<BR>


Replace brown sugar with honey or omit the brown sugar and<BR>
 	cinnamon and fill the center with "red hot" candies.</P></B>

<P>Copyright 1996, Enter, Inc. http://www.entermag.com</P></BLOCKQUOTE>

