<HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>Enter Magazine--Reason</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#FF5500"> 
<BR>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG  SRC="reasonhead.jpeg"></P>
<BR>
<BR>


<BLOCKQUOTE>


<P><A HREF="MAILTO:enter@entermag.com">By Bill Thornbro</A></P>


<P><FONT SIZE=4>T</FONT>hanks to the courage and common sense of a few judges, the Communications Decency Act has been beaten back for a time. This is no time to get smug, beat chests or claim victory. The censors took a hard shot to the ribs, but the fight, they promise, isn't over. We win round one; round two will be tougher.</P>





<P>Note their posture. Censors never cower, even in the face of a certain whuppin'. Why? There's something about their psychology, about being superior and perfect and always right. Would you back down or slink <!-- Graphic Tag --><IMG WIDTH=342 HEIGHT=269 ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="reasontoon.gif">silently away if you thought civilization itself depended on you and your struggle? You can beat on censors twice a day forever and not win. Like ghoulish extras in a George Romero movie, censors never stay down long.</P>





<P>The First Amendment has survived this long because its guardians have an equally high threshold of pain. God bless our first line of defense, the fearless editors and brave librarians who put their careers on the line to protect our freedom. You should hear some of their war stories. You can't imagine how often these heroes have stood their ground in the face of spineless publishers, wilting library boards or holier-than-thou civic busy bodies. Is there a monument in Washington to the Unknown Librarian? There should be.</P>





<P>These people inspire us to be vigilant. They teach us that censors never rest and neither should we.</P>





<P>Censors keep pace with technology. Life was easy when all they had to do was ban a few books, but the smart censors go wherever there are good ideas. They were quick to attack when movies, radio and television came along. When the Internet came along, censors were ready. They never miss an opportunity to keep you ignorant. </P>





<P>There will more CDAs. The people who claim they want government off your back are the same people who want to suppress your freedom with CDAs. People who advocate deregulation of industry want to regulate your life with CDAs. They would abolish regulations protecting our food and environment while regulating what you read and see.</P>





<P>Don't take your gloves off yet. Expect the bell for round two soon. </P>

</BLOCKQUOTE>
<BR>
<BR>

