<HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>Enter Magazine--Let's Get Postal</TITLE></HEAD>  
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#FFDD00"> 
<BR>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG  SRC="postalhead.jpeg"></P><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE><P>

<P>
Like a lot of graduating seniors, I couldn't wait to start my career. Unfortunately, I had a harder-than-expected time finding a job in my major (social work) and ended up taking a job as a clerk in a liquor store. One thing led to another and I wound up working there nearly six months. It was extreme HELL.</P>

<P>The owner was a Danny DeVito clone with a nasty temper and breath that smelled like a freshly exhumed corpse. To make matters worse, <IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="postal.gif"> Death Mouth liked to munch on peanut butter crackers and barbeque potato chips while bending over the cash register to cough in your face. He would then run his greasy fingers around his gums to dislodge, examine and ultimately re-enjoy any unswallowed orange cud.</P>

<P>The thing that ticked me off most was when he would criticize clerks in front of customers. Turnover was always high, which he blamed on "irresponsible college kids" rather than his abuse and the putrid minimum wage he paid.</P>

<P>Anyway, our store was robbed four times in the six months I was there--twice on my shift. I don't know why I didn't quit the first time. The last time was shortly before Christmas and this guy walked in and pointed a gun at my face. Believe it or not, this guy was kind of polite and even said thanks and "Merry Christmas" when I gave him the money from the register. He was walking backwards out of the store when he hit a display stand, knocking over several bottles of booze. He laughed and said, "There goes the profits." I wished him a happy holiday. When I told the cops the story they all laughed because they hated the owner as much as I did.</P>

<P>When Death Mouth saw the video of the robbery he went through the roof because I was, in his words, "awful damn friendly" with the robber. The video even showed me laughing. Death Mouth was kicking broken glass around the store and cussing before I decided enough was enough. I told him where he could stick a two-liter bottle of club soda and quit on the spot.</P>


<P>A week later I got a good job at a clinic I had applied to months earlier. The best part is Death Mouth called me twice asking me to come back to the liquor store. What a freakin' lunatic. </P>


<P><A HREF="MAILTO:enter@entermag.com"><I>J.B.</I></A></P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<BR>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>It's never too late to enter our <A HREF="workstory.html">work story contest.</A></P>
<BR>
