<HEAD><TITLE>Enter Magazine--Calling Dr. Love</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY LINK="#FF5500" BACKGROUND="back.gif" TEXT="#FFFF55">
<BR>
<BR>

<BLOCKQUOTE>

<P><B>Enter:</B> But do you feel that there's enough time to really help people on the air?</P>





<P><B>Dr. Judy:</B> When I first started in this work it was very, very distressing to me that I couldn't spend hours and hours with each person. Everybody deserves hours. I had to accept that the show is a totality, it's like a group experience. If people don't get their answer answered completely in whatever time we give them, then they get their answer by listening to other people. <IMG WIDTH=300 HEIGHT=299 ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="drjudygene.gif">There are many people who call and say they learned by listening to everybody else. It's a vicarious experience, and a totality, rather than just enough time for everybody.</P>





<P><B>Enter:</B> What about people with serious problems like the caller who only had four months to live and wasn't sure if he should get married?</P>





<P><B>Dr. Judy:</B> [Dr. Judy takes a deep gasp, puts a hand to her chest, places her hand on my shoulder and dramatically leans back.] That was incredible. That was an incredibly beautiful call, because it just showed what <I>Love Phones</I> does, that it's not really just about sex, but to really touch their hearts. And I think it was an important message. A miracle happened on <I>Love Phones</I>.</P>





<P><B>Enter:</B> There was also a caller who you felt was a paranoid schizophrenic, and a couple of minutes doesn't seem like enough time to help someone like that.</P>





<P><B>Dr. Judy:</B> I put people on hold. We have a bunch (of calls we put on hold). We have a whole staff of graduate students who get back to people. We follow them up as much as we can. We take care of them. We do our best. We offer as much as we can.</P>





<P><B>Enter:</B> Do you always follow the advice that you give?</P>





<P><B>Dr. Judy:</B> Yeah. My advice comes from my heart. It just comes through me. Over the years I've been really growing to be authentic, and that is my goal personally and my message to everybody. To totally be yourself. Most books talk about how you should put on games, learn and pretend and wait, and my message is just be yourself. That's what I am on the air. Each day and each night is that challenge to me. I never get tired. I never get depressed, because of the connection to somebody, really heart to heart, it makes me energized not tired.</P>





<P><B>Enter:</B> Are men ever uncomfortable about getting in a relationship with you, because their afraid you'll analyze everything they do?</P>





<P><B>Dr. Judy:</B> They go one of two ways. Either they really want to try it out with the Queen of Sex and Love and test themselves and earn five stars. Or they're intimidated and petrified and scared. </P>

</BLOCKQUOTE>
<BR>
<BR>

