<HEAD><TITLE>Enter Magazine--Ralph: Loud and Clear</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"> 

<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG  SRC="ralphhead.jpeg"></P>



<BLOCKQUOTE><P><!-- Graphic Tag -->
<IMG ALT="W"ALIGN=BASELINE SRC="w.jpeg">hen your star is on the rise, you can say crazy stuff and get away with it. But Rafaela Farias doesn't sound crazy. She sounds full of The Great American Dream, even when she says something really nuts like:
</P>




<P>"If you love what you're doing, money shouldn't matter."</P>





<P>The 28-year-old radio personality is hopelessly sincere. "I DJed at a radio station for four years for no money," she says, and you look at that heart-shaped face, deep into her honey-brown eyes, and you believe her every word and wonder why more people don't work 14 hours a day for black bread and water.</P>





<P>Farias, who goes by the moniker Ralph in real life and Rockin' Ralph on the air at 
<A HREF="http://www.wfbq.com">WFBQ-FM</A> in Indianapolis, combines hard work with equal parts enthusiasm and cuteness. She grins as she describes the handful of national radio commercials she recently recorded, but she positively beams as she explains the source of her work ethic and positive attitude--her parents.</P>





<P>Her Mexican-American parents were migrant farm laborers. They decided they would end the cycle of migrant life. Emilio Farias quit school in the eighth grade to work extra hours in the fields during hot Hoosier harvests, and he later toiled on a car lot before landing a factory job. Ralph's mother, Remigia Nunez, studied hard in high school and turned a love for typing into a scholarship to secretary school. When her family went back to South Texas at season's end, Remigia stayed in Indiana and furthered her education. Emilio and Remigia eventually met and married, settled down in quiet Union City, and raised their children to believe anything is possible if you're willing to work hard.</P>





<P>"To me, the American  Dream is fulfilling your goal, whatever it might be," says Ralph. </P></BLOCKQUOTE>


