<HEAD><TITLE>Enter Magazine--So you wanna be...A Mattress Cop</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"> 


<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG  SRC="matthead.jpeg"></P><BR>
<BR>
<DFN></DFN>

<BLOCKQUOTE><P>
<IMG ALT="Y" IMG ALIGN=BASELINE SRC="y.jpeg">eah, you can see yourself in uniform,  a burly member of the feared Mattress Police, that top-secret division of the Federal Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Box Springs. You'd take a blood oath to uphold the Constitution and to forever preserve the holy image of J. Edgar Hoover--the image we had before we learned the G-Man was a Girlie Man. Maybe you'd get to be a plain-clothes Mattress Dick. You could raid private homes, bust down bedroom doors and violate civil rights willy-nilly (What's a Constitution when you can be featured on Cops?). "Okay," you'd holler, "this is the Mattress Police. You two, stop that coitus right now!" You'd flash your badge so nobody could read it, towering over the probable felons like a California redwood. Then you'd wave your government-issue Uzi in their direction and scream: "Look, which one of you scumbags took off the TAG?"</P>

<!-- Graphic Tag -->
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="matt.jpeg">



<P>Only one problem, officer. There is no Mattress Police. The feds don't care if you remove the tag on your mattress. "The tag" is a requirement of individual state boards of health, not Janet Reno & Co. According to one bedding manufacturer, states require each company to attach a tag that lists the contents (goose down, polyester fibers, etc.) of new pillows and mattresses. "Each ingredient is listed on the tag," a manufacturer said, "along with a number issued to the company by the state.</P>





<P>But what about the famous warning, DO NOT REMOVE UNDER PENALTY OF LAW? "If you read it again you'll notice it says 'not to be removed except by the consumer,'" said another manufacturer, one who has heard this dumb story too many times over the years to be amused. "A lot of comedians tell the joke, but it's really not that funny."        <A HREF="MAILTO:enter@entermag.com">            <IMG SRC="http://www.entermag.com/end.jpeg" BORDER=0 ALIGN=BASELINE></A></BLOCKQUOTE>




<BR>
<BR>


<CENTER><TABLE>
<TR><TD></TD><TD><A HREF="/august/work/worktoc.html"><IMG BORDER=0  SRC="/august/tocart/storywork.gif" ALT="Work"></A></TD><TD WIDTH=5></TD><TD><a href="http://www.entermag.com"><IMG BORDER=0  SRC="/august/tocart/logo.gif" ALT="Enter Magazine's Survival Guide"></A>
</TD><TD></TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>


